[3] France (Nouvelle-Aquitaine)
Date: Mon 12 Feb 2018
Source: France info [in French trans. Corr.SB, edited]
https://france3-regions.francetvinfo.fr/nouvelle-aquitaine/gironde/bordeaux/epidemie-rougeole-nouvelle-aquitaine-213-cas-confirmes-57-malades-hospitalises-1422339.html


The ARS [Regional Health Agency] recommends that all néo-aquitains check their vaccination status.

According to the last count on [6 Feb 2018], the measles epidemic has infected 213 people in Nouvelle-Aquitaine region since the beginning of November 2017, mainly in [the departments of] Vienne and Gironde.

The ARS also reports that 57 patients were hospitalized, more than a quarter of those infected.

"90 percent of cases of measles were not or were poorly vaccinated (2 doses are necessary to be protected)" says the regional health agency, which encourages all New Aquitaine to verify their vaccination [status].

Since the beginning of the epidemic, [cases of] patients have been reported on the Bordeaux [Gironde department] campus and then in primary schools in the city.

Poitou-Charente, several people were infected in Poitiers [Vienne department], and in Limoges [Haute-Vienne department], a case has been recently confirmed.

"Since November 2017, the departments of Gironde and Vienne have been the most affected, but isolated cases of measles can appear anywhere and initiate an epidemic," says the ARS, which also reports some cases in Charente-Maritime, Deux-Sèvres, Dordogne, Landes, and Pyrénées-Atlantiques.

